What is TreeSet?
TreeSet is a class in Java that implements the SortedSet interface and extends AbstractSet.
1-It stores unique elements like any other Set but also maintains elements in sorted order
(natural ordering or via a Comparator).
2-Internally, it is backed by a Red-Black Tree (a balanced binary search tree).
3-Because of this tree structure, it provides logarithmic time complexity (O(log n)) f
or basic operations like add, remove, and contains.

Key Features of TreeSet:
| Feature            | Details                                                                         |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Ordering           | Elements are stored in **sorted ascending order** (natural ordering by default) |
| Allows Duplicates  | No, duplicates are ignored                                                      |
| Allows Null        | **No**, attempting to add `null` throws `NullPointerException`                  |
| Thread Safety      | Not synchronized                                                                |
| Performance        | O(log n) for add, remove, and contains operations                               |
| Additional Methods | Provides methods like `first()`, `last()`, `headSet()`, `tailSet()`, `subSet()` |

When to Use TreeSet?
When you want a set of unique elements sorted automatically.
When you need efficient search, insertion, and removal with ordered traversal.
Useful for applications like leaderboards, range queries, or when sorted data is required without duplicates.

Common Methods of TreeSet
| Method                               | Description                                                                  |
| ------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `add(E e)`                           | Adds element `e` if not already present                                      |
| `remove(Object o)`                   | Removes specified element                                                    |
| `contains(Object o)`                 | Checks if element exists                                                     |
| `first()`                            | Returns the lowest (first) element                                           |
| `last()`                             | Returns the highest (last) element                                           |
| `headSet(E toElement)`               | Returns a view of the portion of this set less than `toElement`              |
| `tailSet(E fromElement)`             | Returns a view of the portion of this set greater or equal to `fromElement`  |
| `subSet(E fromElement, E toElement)` | Returns a view between `fromElement` (inclusive) and `toElement` (exclusive) |
| `size()`                             | Returns number of elements                                                   |
| `isEmpty()`                          | Checks if set is empty                                                       |
| `clear()`                            | Removes all elements                                                         |
